So it was with this mini-series of CYB3RGRACES, which originally and after the completion of the first painting 'Grace of Faith' was to become part of the '2084' series. As it turned out, however, the intention was to develop an independent series with unmistakable stylistic elements of the great designer and painter Alphonse Mucha. Mucha is known to me since early days as a special artist, who set new standards with his aesthetics and the claim on my part was to successfully achieve an amalgamation of certain Art Deco elements with a haunting Cyberpunk style. The result: the graces."

Cryptoarg is a digital art collective uniting Argentinian artists of the likes of Frenetik Void, Milton Sanz, Fede Bona and Crypt0baby. This massive collaborative project brings together 23 thriving artists and their unique visions on the concept of CHAOS. CHAOS can be understood as a driving force of nature, a logic hidden deep within mathematics, a philosophy of life or a counterpoint to order and civility. Chaos is deeply rooted in all creative endeavors as a necessary energy for change. We live through and survive chaos in our daily lives, and we try to interpret it to understand the universe around us. As artists from a developing country, these creators live surrounded by chaos, sometimes struggling with it, sometimes thriving from it. Each artwork in this project is a creative interpretation with the individual perspective of each artist, creating a once in a lifetime compendium that brings a new perspective on the possibilities and perils of CHAOS.
